re\nfunctions. Comparison with recent data at z<0.7 shows reasonable agreement with\na model that assumes a median entropy floor of K0=200 keV sq.cm. When\nobservations are extended to group scales (kT < 1 keV), this evolution will\nhave the potential to discriminate between an entropy floor that is independent\nof redshift (for example, in a preheating scenario) and one that depends on the\ncooling time of the halo.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 28 Nov 2005 17:29:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 3 Jan 2006 22:25:11 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-13"}
